works.description: Volkswagen’s Bugatti Veyron 16.4, which got worldwide fame as the fastest production car in the world, is now bringing an end to its limited edition production of 300 pieces with the last buyer from Europe. An automotive marvel in every way possible, the Bugatti Veyron was to be created in limited numbers. This has been a tradition with other Bugatti cars such as the Supersport which are collector’s items and rated as the most valuable cars in existence.
